This is a nice clash, but you mention in the statement about how division isn't valid when Y is 0, but then there are no test cases with any of the inputs being 0, so it's not even needed to worry about.

It would be good to remove that line and just mention in the constraints that none of them are ever 0. This is very useful for Shortest mode, but also for Fastest mode (since you can save time not worrying about that edge case).
I have taken the liberty to edit the contribution to remove the extra space at the end of Validator 4 which could be problematic in some languages.

This is my lua:
next_token = string.gmatch(io.read(), "[^%s]+")
operators = {"+","-","*","/"}
A,B,C,D=tonumber(next_token()),tonumber(next_token()),tonumber(next_token()),tonumber(next_token())
op={}
matched = false
for _, op1 in pairs(operators) do
    for __, op2 in pairs(operators) do
        load("if A"..op1.."B == C"..op2.."D then matched = true end")()
        if matched then
            op[1] = op1
            op[2] = op2
            break 
        end
    end
    if matched then
        break 
    end
end
if #op > 0 then
    print(table.concat(op," "))
else
    print("-1")
end

a) + +

maybe it should be added on statement that the operators for the solution are unique.
